    <div class="religion">
      <p>
        <h3>Religion</h3>
        Protestants make up 70% of the population in the area, followed by Orthodox Christians (16.8%), Traditionalists (3.8%), Muslims (4.9%), Catholics (3.4%), and others (1.1%).[1] The native Anuak people have historically resided in Gambela.</p>
